posts.raw_content:
https://www.blueletterbible.org/lexicon/g2889/kjv/tr/0-1/

>2889. kosmos ►
Strong's Lexicon
kosmos: World, universe, order, adornment
Original Word: κόσμος
Part of Speech: Noun, Masculine
Transliteration: kosmos
Pronunciation: KOS-mos
Phonetic Spelling: (kos'-mos)
Definition: World, universe, order, adornment
Meaning: the world, universe; worldly affairs; the inhabitants of the world; adornment.
Word Origin: Derived from a primary verb κομέω (koméō), meaning "to take care of" or "to order."

>Mat 4:8 - Again, the devil taketh him up into an exceeding high mountain, and sheweth him all the kingdoms of the world, G2889 and the glory of them;

The devil is ingrained in the Adamic kósmos.   Jesus Christ was not of the devil influenced adamic kósmos. The kósmos was all around Jesus Christ,  and He was it's light.

>Mat 5:14 - Ye are the light of the world. G2889 A city that is set on an hill cannot be hid.

The followers of God by the Spirit brought by Jesus Christ, become the light of the kósmos. 

>Jhn 15:19 - If ye were of the world, G2889 the world G2889 would love his own: but because ye are not of the world, G2889 but I have chosen you out of the world, G2889 therefore the world G2889 hateth you.

If the Christian is not of this kósmos,  they must be of another kósmos.   The kósmos of God is where the children of God dwell.  The Christian can say, I am not of this world,  I am of God's word,  the kósmos of God, and the kósmos in Jesus Christ.   

>Jhn 17:14 - I have given them thy word; and the world G2889 hath hated them, because they are not of the world, G2889 even as I am not of the world. G2889

The Christian is above this world in the kingdom of God.  The Christian learns to dwell in the Spirit,  in Christ. 

>Eph 2:2 - Wherein in time past ye walked according to the course of this world, G2889 according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit that now worketh in the children of disobedience:

When Jesus Christ comes, he brings a new kósmos to those that put faith in His life and reign. The old kósmos is still here, but the Christian doesn't walk in subjection to the devil influenced Adamic kósmos. 

>Revelation 15:2 And I saw as it were a sea of glass mingled with fire: and them that had gotten the victory over the beast, and over his image, and over his mark, and over the number of his name, stand on the sea of glass, having the harps of God.

The whole purpose of the book of Revelation is that the individual soul learns to triumph over the carnal adamic kósmos.  The Christian triumphs "in Christ".  Jesus Christ brings the new creation kósmos to each Christian soul.

>Revelation 21:5 And he that sat upon the throne said, Behold, I make all things new. And he said unto me, Write: for these words are true and faithful. 6 And he said unto me, It is done. I am Alpha and Omega, the beginning and the end. I will give unto him that is athirst of the fountain of the water of life freely. 7 He that overcometh(triumphs) shall inherit all things; and I will be his God, and he shall be my son. <<------ in the kósmos kingdom of God and His Christ. 

>Revelation 11:15 And the seventh angel sounded; and there were great voices in heaven, saying, The kingdoms of this world are become the kingdoms of our Lord, and of his Christ; and he shall reign for ever and ever.
